question: Match List-I and List-II with respect to proteins and their functions and select the correct option.
1. Collagen -> s. Intercellular ground substance
2. Trypsin -> r. Enzyme
3. Insulin -> q. Hormone
4. Antibody -> p. Fights infectious agents
explanation: Collagen is ground substance. Trypsin is an enzyme. Insulin is a hormone. Antibodies fight infections.
